Body: Description: File Server Activity appears to be failing to import into the database. I have included additional details in the comments of the ticket.

*If you are unable to reach the client, or the ticket is going into a no-response status, please let me know.*

 

Issue: Data does not appear to be importing properly into the databases, reports are not loading.

 

Netwrix Enterpriser Auditor Version: 11.5

When loading the AIC we noticed that they appear to be having issues importing data from their audited file server endpoints.

  • LMGRISILON - Last imported 12/10/2021

 

Error messages states 'Process aborted'

 

When reviewing their Activity Monitor, we are showing activity from today.

  • Activity Monitor version: 6.0.12

 

Activity Does not appear to be being imported into the database.

 

If you have any further question, please let me know.

 

-Thank You
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Ian Ranstrom, Alex Mata

Steps to Reproduce Updated: Open AIC
Select File system
Last scan shows as 2021

What We've Learned Updated: --------
03/04/2025
--------
FSAA scan has been disabled and does not appear to have run since 2021.
We setup a new schedule to let it run overnight and will follow up tomorrow.
Next Steps Updated: Let FSAA scans run overnight and verify that the scan is working and importing.

What We've Learned Updated: --------
03/14/2025
--------
Bulk import was hitting the error "Tier 2 database does not match Tier 1 data"
We ran the FSAA RESET maintenance task for the host and restarted bulk import. The bulk import appears to be working and we will wait to verify it completes.

--------
03/04/2025
--------
FSAA scan has been disabled and does not appear to have run since 2021.
We setup a new schedule to let it run overnight and will follow up tomorrow.
Next Steps Updated: Awaiting results of bulk import job.
